Content-Transfer-Encoding: 8bit

## Changes

### Migration 013
- Add role (TEXT, default 'member'), is_active (INTEGER, default 1),
  display_name (TEXT nullable) to users table
- Promote system_default_user to role='admin'
- Add registration_mode and registration_domain to system_settings for
  configurable registration policy (invite_only | domain_allowlist | open)

### User model & repository
- User struct gains role, is_active, display_name fields
- IUserRepository gains create_user_full, set_active, set_role, set_display_name
- create_user delegates to create_user_full with role='member'
- ensure_system_user explicitly inserts role='admin' on fresh databases
- set_system_user_credentials preserves role='admin'

### System settings
- SystemSettings gains registration_mode, registration_domain fields
- effective_registration_mode() helper defaults to 'invite_only'
- upsert_settings re-fetches row to preserve independently-set fields

### API types
- PublicUser gains role, is_active, display_name
- New: AdminCreateUserRequest, AdminUpdateUserRequest, AdminResetPasswordRequest
- New: RegisterRequest for policy-governed self-registration

### Auth middleware
- CurrentUser gains role field
- auth_middleware rejects is_active=false accounts with 403
- require_admin_middleware: 403 if role != 'admin'
- local mode injects role='admin' for --local bypass

### Admin routes
- GET/POST /api/admin/users — list and invite-create users (admin only)
- PATCH /api/admin/users/:id — update role/is_active/display_name
- POST /api/admin/users/:id/reset-password — admin force-reset
- POST /api/auth/register — public, governed by registration_mode setting

### Router wiring
- admin_routes mounted alongside auth_routes in main router
- AuthRouterState gains settings_repo (Arc<dyn ISettingsRepository>)

### Tests
- All new repository methods covered with integration tests
- require_admin_middleware: member→403, admin→200
- route_tests updated with settings_repo in AuthRouterState
- middleware_tests updated with role field in CurrentUser
